diff:1415018024:1413977454:=23c23,29%0a%3c Commotion Wireless firmware handles autoconfiguration of IP addressing for all interfaces of the radios.%0a---%0a> Until such a time as zeroconf for the interfaces has been done, the address for the backbone interface should be in the 10.0.0.0/8 network.  This allows us to make every octet available for hosts, more or less ensuring we have ample supply of addresses to cover Buffalo, and much later, WNY.%0a> %0a> Client-facing interfaces (Such as the gateway address for client APs) should be 192.168.X.0/16.%0a> %0a> The client-facing interface shall use the same number in it's second octet that is in the last octet of backbone address.  As an example, a mesh node at 10.0.0.10 should use 192.168.10.0 as it's client-facing address, in order to facilitate routing across interfaces.  If this is not followed, all traffic from the client LAN shall be NAT'd in some form, as to not poison routing tables.%0a> %0a> The network coordinator should be approached for an address, as this person is able to quickly determine what nodes connected to BUFFALOMESH have taken which address.%0a
